> I thought that HN had a policy where the titles used are taken verbatim from the page being linked to, unless they&#x27;re so completely terrible that an alternative title is needed.<p>It seems that&#x27;s the intent expressed in the HN Guidelines (<a href="https://news.ycombinator.com/newsguidelines.html" rel="nofollow">https://news.ycombinator.com/newsguidelines.html</a>):<p>&quot;Please don&#x27;t do things to make titles stand out, like using uppercase or exclamation points, or adding a parenthetical remark saying how great an article is. It&#x27;s implicit in submitting something that you think it&#x27;s important.
...
Otherwise please use the original title, unless it is misleading or linkbait.&quot;
